Food was delicious.  I really enjoyed the jerk chicken and the curry goat.  Rice and peas were on point.  And the cabbage was delicious too.  Beef Patties and the coco bread....check!!!  The Mac n Cheese was bland AF though.  It looked good but didn't taste as good as it looked.  But you don't go to Jamaican spots to get Mac n cheese anyway.  I just tried it to see if they could do that too.  Overall, it was wonderful food and the place is very clean.  Best Jerk wings I've had in DC.

The three people behind the counter were friendly and very helpful.  The heavyset man was sweating profusely and they all talked over the food while preparing the contents.  That should have been a clue that I was going to be disappointed with the entire food content.  The food was extremely upsetting.  The macaroni and cheese tasted very spoiled, the jerk chicken was salty and disgusting, the plantains were tough and very bad looking, the oxtail had no pepper or butter beans and was just very bad.
